HEADWORD: Commote
<hw>Com*mote"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Commove</er>.]</ety> <def>To commove; to disturb; to stir up.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Society being more or less <qex>commoted</qex> and made
uncomfortable.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commotion</ent>⟦br⟧
